laboratory_examinations.findings: Vitamin D insufficiency [25(OH) vitamin D = 20 ng/mL, reference range 30â€“70 ng/mL], normal levels of parathyroid hormone 34.6 pg/mL, fibroblast growth factor 23 (FGF-23) 72 pg/mL, alkaline phosphatase 158 U/L, calcium 8.8 mg/dL, and phosphorus 5.0 mg/dL.
Extensive heterotopic ossification involving soft tissues and muscles surrounding the bilateral humeri and proximal ulnae, bilateral femurs, and bilateral tibias/fibulas.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Computed tomography of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis
laboratory_examinations.findings: Extensive ossifications of the muscles including the right latissimus dorsi, left scalene, bilateral pectoralis, bilateral external oblique abdominal, right iliacus, bilateral gluteal, left adductor, and left hamstring. Also involvement of subcutaneous tissues of the right upper back and left lower quadrant of the abdomen, left posterior sacral region, bilateral hips, and along the fascia superficial to the erector spinae muscles, extending to the skin, with no evidence of pulmonary fibrosis. No abnormal ossifications were seen in the bony structures.
Revealed a novel de novo heterozygous, likely pathogenic variant in the FAM111B (c.1462delT, p.Cys488Valfs*21) in the proband.
